references: Finally, Table II suggests an important and practical trade-off in the proposed FL setting: server can select more clients at each communication round while having each of them communicate less, and obtain the same accuracy as using fewer clients, but having each of them communicate more. The former may be preferable when many clients are available, but each has very limited upload bandwidth which is a setting common in practice.
